  "details": "UltraISO 9.7.1.3519 contains a local buffer overflow vulnerability in the Output FileName field of the Make CD/DVD Image dialog that allows attackers to overwrite SEH and SE handler records. Attackers can craft a malicious filename string with 304 bytes of data followed by SEH record overwrite values and paste it into the Output FileName field to trigger a denial of service crash.",
